# Vue & Composables Patterns

## Single File Components

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
// Prefer composables over inline logic
import { useAuthGuard } from "@/composables/useAuthGuard";

const { isAuthenticated } = useAuthGuard();
</script>
```

- **Options API:** do not use for new code
- Explicit `.vue` extension on imports: `import HeaderLayout from "@/components/HeaderLayout.vue"`
- Colocate page-specific components; shared ones in `components/`

## Key components

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `HeaderLayout.vue` | Main app header with actions |
| `AuthLayout.vue` | Centered auth page wrapper |
| `I18nSwitcher.vue` | Flag-based locale switcher |
| `HeaderProfileLink.vue` | Avatar → profile link |
| `ThemeToggle.vue` | Dark/light mode switch |
| `AppLogo.vue` | Manifest PNG logo |
| `FbButton.vue` / `FbInput.vue` / … | Flowbite-styled primitives in `components/flowbite/` |

## Composables

| Composable | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| `useAuthGuard.ts` | Client-side auth state + redirects |
| `useNotifications.ts` | Fetch + display notifications |
| `useSocket.ts` | Realtime connection (Echo or Socket.IO) |
| `useAdminUsers.ts` | Admin user CRUD operations |

- One composable per concern; return reactive refs and methods
- Clean up subscriptions in `onUnmounted`

## Nitro server routes

File naming convention — HTTP verb suffix:

```
server/api/auth/login.post.ts
server/api/auth/me.get.ts
server/api/auth/refresh.put.ts
server/api/auth/logout.post.ts
```

- These proxy to the backend API; keep them thin
- Use `defineEventHandler` + `$fetch` pattern

## Realtime

```typescript
const { connect, disconnect, on, off } = useSocket();

// REALTIME_DRIVER=echo  → Laravel Echo
// REALTIME_DRIVER=socketio → socket.io-client
```

- Listen for `v1.user.admin.*` events on private `user.{id}` channel
- PWA splash screen links: `lib/pwa-splash-links.ts`

## Pinia stores

- Stores in `stores/` — one per domain (`useAuthStore`, etc.)
- Use `storeToRefs` when destructuring reactive state in components
- Do not duplicate data that `@sidebase/nuxt-auth` session already provides

## Shared API types

- Admin types in `types/admin/` — shared contract with Next.js sibling
- Error shape: `{ detail: [...] }` (422) or `{ message }` (4xx/5xx)
- Pagination: `{ data, meta, links }`

## Common pitfalls (avoid)

| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| SSR 401 auth loop | Keep `disableServerSideAuth: true` |
| Dashboard after logout | Call `clearAuthCookies()` on logout |
| Using `libs/` folder | Use `lib/` (singular) — project convention |
| Manual Vue/Nuxt imports | Use auto-imports via `#imports` |
| Options API for new features | Use `<script setup lang="ts">` + composables |
